First, $f(x+h) = (x+h)^{2} = x^{2} + 2xh + h^{2}$. Then
\[
 \frac{f(x+h) - f(x)}{h} 
 = \frac{(x^{2} + 2xh + h^{2}) - x^{2}}{h} 
 = \frac{2xh + h^{2}}{h} 
 = 2x + h.
\]
This expression will appear again in [ch:derivative] when we define the 
derivative of $f(x) = x^{2}$. For now, practice the algebra.
